column3: This is very spammy though, compared to normal -benchmark...\n

Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/p4001_e21efd5de061cd005385932d3058b79323e4b217/ for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-te
I'm not convinced of the need of adding per-function benchmark functionality to bitcoind. In principle the same (and better) could be done with a profiler.\n
@sipa If you agree @laanwj you are free to just close this, so we can go on :).\n
Yeah, I think there's little benefit here.\n
